  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Cut the zucchinis into 1-inch (2.5 cm) thick slices.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together the olive oil, garlic, ginger, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the zucchini slices to the bowl and toss to coat with the marinade.",
    "Let the zucchini marinate for at least 30 minutes.",
    "Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.",
    "Arrange the zucchini slices on the baking sheet in a single layer.",
    "Roast the zucchini in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes, or until tender and lightly browned.",
    "Garnish with chopped fresh parsley, mint, and sumac (if using).",
    "Serve hot.",
    "Adjust the seasoning as needed."
